    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1970-06-15T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1970-06-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="194"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d194">
                <head>194. Memorandum From the President’s Assistant for National Security Affairs
                        (<persName corresp="#p_KHA1" type="from">Kissinger</persName>) to Secretary
                    of Defense <persName corresp="#p_LMR2" type="to">Laird</persName>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d194fn1">Source: National Archives, Nixon
                        Presidential Materials, <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Files, <gloss
                            target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Institutional Files (H-Files), Boxes H–212
                        and H–213, <gloss target="#t_NSDM1">NSDM</gloss> 35. Secret.</note>
                    <note n="2" type="summary" xml:id="d194fn2">
                        <persName corresp="#p_KHA1">Kissinger</persName> asked <persName
                            corresp="#p_LMR2">Laird</persName> for Defense’s recommendations on the
                        destruction of biological weapons and the transfer of biological weapons
                        facilities.</note>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1970-06-15"
                        >June 15, 1970</date>
                </dateline>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT:</head>
                    <item>Implementation of National Security Decision Memoranda 35 and 44</item>
                </list>
                <p>With reference to National Security Decision Memoranda 35 and 44, the President
                    has asked that recommendations regarding the destruction of biological
                    agents/weapons and toxin agents/weapons be submitted for his consideration by
                    June 30, 1970.</p>
                <p>Additionally, the President has requested that any other recommendations
                    regarding implementation of the decision to confine the United States biological
                    program to research for defensive purposes only (e.g., alternative uses of
                    biological facilities) be submitted for his consideration at the same time.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_KHA1">Henry A. Kissinger</persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
